# UI Layout & Sidebar

The main application layout is controlled by `[App.js](mdc:src/App.js)` and uses a 2x2 CSS Grid for precise alignment and responsiveness.

```javascript
<div style={{
  display: 'grid',
  gridTemplateColumns: '280px 1fr', // Left column for sidebar, right for questions
  gridTemplateRows: 'auto 1fr',    // Top row for title, bottom for content
  gap: '0 24px',
  alignItems: 'start',
}}>
  {/* Top-left cell (empty spacer) */}
  <div></div>

  {/* Top-right cell (Basic Information Title) */}
  {...}

  {/* Bottom-left cell (Sidebar) */}
  <div style={{ position: 'sticky', top: '20px' }}>
    <SidebarResults />
  </div>

  {/* Bottom-right cell (Questions) */}
  {...}
</div>
```

-   **Sidebar**: The `[SidebarResults.js](mdc:src/SidebarResults.js)` component is placed in the bottom-left grid cell.
-   **Sticky Behavior**: The sidebar's "sticky" positioning is applied to its container `div` within the `App.js` grid, ensuring it stays fixed during scrolling while maintaining perfect alignment with the main content area.
-   **Title Alignment**: The "Basic Information" title is moved out of `[MetaQuestionsSection.js](mdc:src/MetaQuestionsSection.js)` and placed directly in the top-right grid cell in `App.js` to ensure alignment.